{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e71f331f-c04e-4a96-8df2-41cd292b2914","content":"Here's your current project and what it becomes with MSTest.Sdk:\n\n**Current:**\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"Microsoft.NET.Sdk\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <IsPackable>false</IsPackable>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest.TestFramework\" Version=\"2.2.10\" />\n    <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest.TestAdapter\" Version=\"2.2.10\" />\n    <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"17.5.0\" />\n  </ItemGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**Converted:**\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.7.3\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\nKey changes:\n\n1. **SDK** → `MSTest.Sdk/3.7.3` replaces `Microsoft.NET.Sdk`\n2. **All 3 PackageReferences removed** — the SDK brings in `MSTest.TestFramework`, `MSTest.TestAdapter`, and `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` automatically\n3. **`IsPackable` removed** — MSTest.Sdk sets this to `false` by default\n\nWant me to apply this change to your project file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3f970222-1651-402b-aebf-72d233d5b608","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to convert to MSTest.Sdk. MSTest.Sdk replaces:\n1. The `Microsoft.NET.Sdk` SDK with `MSTest.Sdk`\n2. All three MSTest-related PackageReference items (MSTest.TestFramework, MSTest.TestAdapter, Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk)\n\nWith MSTest.Sdk, you just set the SDK and optionally specify a version. The SDK handles all the test dependencies automatically.\n\nLet me convert the project file.","outputTokens":485},"id":"aebd5648-f95c-417f-b46b-3a2dd7d31543","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:21:02.575Z","parentId":"dbfc79e0-b426-47e5-acc9-1c7200d2dc6d"}
